verses.text:
Restore, my dear Savior,
The light of thy face;
Thy soul-cheering comfort impart;
And let the sweet longing
For thy holy place
Bring hope to my desolate heart.

Angels, messengers from heaven,
Come to earth once more;
Bring to men the glorious gospel;
Priceless truths restore.
Let all hear who live today!
This is life, the truth, the way.
Shout hosanna to his name;
One and all his might proclaim.

Tho Zion&rsquo;s foes have counseled deep,
Although they bind with fetters strong,
The God of Jacob does not sleep;
His vengeance will not slumber long;
His vengeance will not slumber long.

Humbly kneeling, sweet appealing&mdash;
&rsquo;Twas the boy&rsquo;s first uttered prayer&mdash;
When the pow&rsquo;rs of sin assailing
Filled his soul with deep despair;
But undaunted, still he trusted
In his Heav&rsquo;nly Father&rsquo;s care,
But undaunted, still he trusted
In his Heav&rsquo;nly Father&rsquo;s care.

Rise and lift up Zion&rsquo;s standard;
Tell our Father&rsquo;s children now:
Heaven&rsquo;s blessed King approaches;
All men must before him bow.

I spied him where a fountain burst
Clear from the rock; his strength was gone.
The heedless water mocked his thirst;
He heard it, saw it hurrying on.
I ran and raised the suff&rsquo;rer up;
Thrice from the stream he drained my cup,
Dipped and returned it running o&rsquo;er;
I drank and never thirsted more.

Then in a moment to my view
The stranger started from disguise.
The tokens in his hands I knew;
The Savior stood before mine eyes.
He spake, and my poor name he named,
&ldquo;Of me thou hast not been ashamed.
These deeds shall thy memorial be;
Fear not, thou didst them unto me.&rdquo;

Come, come, ye Saints, no toil nor labor fear;
But with joy wend your way.
Though hard to you this journey may appear,
Grace shall be as your day.
&rsquo;Tis better far for us to strive
Our useless cares from us to drive;
Do this, and joy your hearts will swell&mdash;
All is well! All is well!

We&rsquo;ll find the place which God for us prepared,
Far away in the West,
Where none shall come to hurt or make afraid;
There the Saints will be blessed.
We&rsquo;ll make the air with music ring,
Shout praises to our God and King;
Above the rest these words we&rsquo;ll tell&mdash;
All is well! All is well!

For the strength of the hills we bless thee,
Our God, our fathers&rsquo; God;
Thou hast made thy children mighty
By the touch of the mountain sod.
Thou hast led thy chosen Israel
To freedom&rsquo;s last abode;

At the hands of foul oppressors
We&rsquo;ve borne and suffered long;
Thou hast been our help in weakness,
And thy pow&rsquo;r hath made us strong.
Amid ruthless foes outnumbered
In weariness we trod;

We are watchers of a beacon
Whose light must never die;
We are guardians of an altar
&rsquo;Midst the silence of the sky.
Here the rocks yield founts of courage,
Struck forth as by thy rod;

Lo! in the desert the flowers are springing;
Streams, ever copious, are gliding along.
Loud from the mountaintops echoes are ringing;
Wastes rise in verdure and mingle in song.

In the furnace God may prove thee,
Thence to bring thee forth more bright,
But can never cease to love thee;
Thou art precious in his sight.
God is with thee, God is with thee;
Thou shalt triumph in his might.

Beautiful Zion, built above;
Beautiful city that I love;
Beautiful gates of pearly white;
Beautiful temple&mdash;God its light;
He who was slain on Calvary
Opens those pearly gates for me.

Zion, Zion, lovely Zion;
Beautiful Zion;
Zion, city of our God!

Beautiful heav&rsquo;n, where all is light;
Beautiful angels clothed in white;
Beautiful strains that never tire;
Beautiful harps thru all the choir;
There shall I join the chorus sweet,
Worshiping at the Savior&rsquo;s feet.

Zion, Zion, lovely Zion;
Beautiful Zion;
Zion, city of our God!

Beautiful crowns on ev&rsquo;ry brow;
Beautiful palms the conq&rsquo;rors show;
Beautiful robes the ransomed wear;
Beautiful all who enter there;
Thither I press with eager feet;
There shall my rest be long and sweet.

Zion, Zion, lovely Zion;
Beautiful Zion;
Zion, city of our God!

Father, all my heart I give thee;
All my service shall be thine.
Guide me as I search in weakness;
Let thy loving light be mine.

Hear me as I pray in meekness;
Let my strength be as thy day.
Give me faith, the greater knowledge;
Father, bless me as I pray.

The rays that shine from Zion&rsquo;s hill
Shall lighten ev&rsquo;ry land;
The King who reigns in Salem&rsquo;s tow&rsquo;r
Shall all the world command.
Among the nations he shall judge;
His judgments truth shall guide;
His scepter shall protect the just
And quell the sinner&rsquo;s pride.

Swiftly flee the clouds of darkness;
Speedily the mists retire;
Nature&rsquo;s universal blackness
Is consumed by heav&rsquo;nly fire,
Is consumed by heav&rsquo;nly fire.

Mine eyes have seen the glory of the coming of the Lord;
He is trampling out the vintage where the grapes of wrath are stored.
He hath loosed the fateful lightning of his terrible, swift sword;
His truth is marching on.

May we labor in the kingdom&mdash;
By the prophets long foretold&mdash;
Where the children of the promise
Shall be gathered in the fold.

He loves the Saints&mdash;he knows them well&mdash;
But turns the wicked down to hell.
Thy God, O Zion, ever reigns;
Praise him in everlasting strains.

Strengthened by thee for the conflict with sin,
Onward we&rsquo;ll press till life&rsquo;s battle we&rsquo;ll win;
Then in thy glory forever we&rsquo;ll stay;
Never from thee will we stray!

Press on, enduring in the ways of Christ.
His love proclaim thru days of mortal strife.
Thus saith our God: &ldquo;Ye have eternal life!&rdquo;

Thou art our rock, our fortress, and our might;
Thou, Lord, our captain in the well-fought fight;
Thou, in the darkness drear, our one true light.

Oh, may our songs to thy courts ascend;
Pleasing to thee may our voices blend.
Lead us as thou hast the faithful led;
Feed us with knowledge and daily bread.
Let us not stray from the paths of truth;
Forgive the folly and faults of youth.
Father, accept thou the songs of praise
Which from our hearts unto thee we raise.

We gather together to ask the Lord&rsquo;s blessing;
He chastens, and hastens his will to make known;
The wicked oppressing now cease from distressing.
Sing praises to his name;
He forgets not his own.

Beside us to guide us, our God with us joining,
Ordaining, maintaining his kingdom divine;
So from the beginning the fight we were winning;
Thou, Lord, wast at our side;
All glory be thine!

Lead, kindly Light, amid th&rsquo;encircling gloom;
Lead thou me on!
The night is dark, and I am far from home;
Lead thou me on!
Keep thou my feet; I do not ask to see
The distant scene&mdash;one step enough for me.

I need thee, oh, I need thee;
Ev&rsquo;ry hour I need thee!
Oh, bless me now, my Savior;
I come to thee!

