I come to thee!

Nearer, dear Savior, to thee,
Nearer, nearer to thee&mdash;
Ever I&rsquo;m striving to be
Nearer, yet nearer to thee!
Trusting, in thee I confide;
Hoping, in thee I abide.

Nearer, dear Savior, to thee,
Nearer, nearer to thee&mdash;
Proved by my trials, I&rsquo;ll be
Nearer, yet nearer to thee!
Humbly I come to thee now;
Earnest, I prayerfully bow.

Other refuge have I none;
Hangs my helpless soul on thee.
Leave, oh, leave me not alone;
Still support and comfort me.
All my trust on thee is stayed;
All my help from thee I bring.
Cover my defenseless head
With the shadow of thy wing.

Jesus, Savior, pilot me
Over life&rsquo;s tempestuous sea;
Unknown waves before me roll,
Hiding rock and treach&rsquo;rous shoal.
Chart and compass came from thee;
Jesus, Savior, pilot me.

As a mother stills her child,
Thou canst hush the ocean wild;
Boist&rsquo;rous waves obey thy will
When thou say&rsquo;st to them, &ldquo;Be still!&rdquo;
Wondrous Sov&rsquo;reign of the sea,
Jesus, Savior, pilot me.

Not the labors of my hands
Can fill all thy law&rsquo;s demands;
Could my zeal no respite know,
Could my tears forever flow,
All for sin could not atone;
Thou must save, and thou alone.

The God who rules on high
And all the earth surveys&mdash;
Who rides upon the stormy sky
And calms the roaring seas&mdash;

Lift up your hearts in praise to God;
Let your rejoicings never cease.
Though tribulations rage abroad,
Christ says, &ldquo;In me ye shall have peace.&rdquo;
Christ says, &ldquo;In me ye shall have peace.&rdquo;

Though Satan rage, &rsquo;tis all in vain;
The words the ancient prophet spoke
Sure as the throne of God remain;
Nor men nor devils can revoke.
Nor men nor devils can revoke.

Be still, my soul: The Lord is on thy side;
With patience bear thy cross of grief or pain.
Leave to thy God to order and provide;
In ev&rsquo;ry change he faithful will remain.
Be still, my soul: Thy best, thy heav&rsquo;nly Friend
Thru thorny ways leads to a joyful end.

Let your heart be not faint
Now the journey&rsquo;s begun;
There is One who still beckons to you.
So look upward in joy
And take hold of his hand;
He will lead you to heights that are new&mdash;

Help us to resist temptation;
Help us to refrain from ill.
Help us all to gain salvation;
Help us all to do thy will.
Help us all to do thy will.

God be with you till we meet again;
By his counsels guide, uphold you;
With his sheep securely fold you.
God be with you till we meet again.

God be with you till we meet again;
Keep love&rsquo;s banner floating o&rsquo;er you;
Smite death&rsquo;s threat&rsquo;ning wave before you.
God be with you till we meet again.

&ldquo;Did not our hearts within us burn?&rdquo;
We know the Spirit&rsquo;s fire is here.
It makes our souls for service yearn;
It makes the path of duty clear.
Lord, may it prompt us, day by day,
In all we do, in all we say.

Now the day is over;
Night is drawing nigh;
Shadows of the evening
Steal across the sky.

Lord, we come before thee now;
At thy feet we humbly bow.
Do not thou our suit disdain;
Shall we seek thee, Lord, in vain?

Abide with me; &rsquo;tis eventide.
The day is past and gone;
The shadows of the evening fall;
The night is coming on.
Within my heart a welcome guest,
Within my home abide.

O Savior, stay this night with me;
Behold, &rsquo;tis eventide.
O Savior, stay this night with me;
Behold, &rsquo;tis eventide.

