He passed the portals of the grave;
Salvation was his song;
He called upon the sinbound soul
To join the heav&rsquo;nly throng.

The King of Kings left worlds of light,
Became the meek and lowly One;
In brightest day or darkest night,
He said, &ldquo;Thy will, O Lord, be done.&rdquo;

&ldquo;Father, from me remove this cup.
Yet, if thou wilt, I&rsquo;ll drink it up.
I&rsquo;ve done the work thou gavest me,
I&rsquo;ve done the work thou gavest me;
Receive my spirit unto thee.&rdquo;

Oh, come, let us adore him;
Oh, come, let us adore him;
Oh, come, let us adore him,
Christ, the Lord.

&mdash; Sing, choirs of angels,
Sing in exultation;
&mdash;&nbsp;Sing, all ye citizens of heav&rsquo;n above!
Glory to God,
Glory in the highest;

Oh, come, let us adore him;
Oh, come, let us adore him;
Oh, come, let us adore him,
Christ, the Lord.

&mdash; Yea, Lord, we greet thee,
Born this happy morning;
&mdash;&nbsp;Jesus, to thee be all glory giv&rsquo;n.
Son of the Father,
Now in flesh appearing;

Oh, come, let us adore him;
Oh, come, let us adore him;
Oh, come, let us adore him,
Christ, the Lord.

