And now the foe advancing,
That valiant host assails,
And yet they never falter;
Their courage never fails.
Their Leader calls, &ldquo;Be faithful!&rdquo;
They pass the word along;
They see his signal flashing
And shout their joyful song:

Then don&rsquo;t stand idly looking on;
The fight with sin is real.
It will be long but must go on;
Put your shoulder to the wheel.

Out of ev&rsquo;ry nation surging&mdash;
Sons of Joseph, Israel&rsquo;s band&mdash;
Now they spread salvation&rsquo;s message
In the tongues of ev&rsquo;ry land.

Come, ye nations, out of darkness;
&rsquo;Tis the time of Christ&rsquo;s return.
Heed the Restoration&rsquo;s message;
Let its light within you burn.

We will work out our salvation;
We will cleave unto the truth;
We will watch and pray and labor
With the fervent zeal of youth. Yes!

We a war &rsquo;gainst sin are waging;
We&rsquo;re contending for the right.
Ev&rsquo;ry day the battle&rsquo;s raging;
Help us, Lord, to win the fight.

Hope of Israel, rise in might
With the sword of truth and right;
Sound the war-cry, &ldquo;Watch and pray!&rdquo;
Vanquish ev&rsquo;ry foe today.

Hope of Israel, rise in might
With the sword of truth and right;
Sound the war-cry, &ldquo;Watch and pray!&rdquo;
Vanquish ev&rsquo;ry foe today.

Strike for Zion, down with error;
Flash the sword above the foe!
Ev&rsquo;ry stroke disarms a foeman;
Ev&rsquo;ry step we conq&rsquo;ring go.

Hope of Israel, rise in might
With the sword of truth and right;
Sound the war-cry, &ldquo;Watch and pray!&rdquo;
Vanquish ev&rsquo;ry foe today.

Soon the battle will be over;
Ev&rsquo;ry foe of truth be down.
Onward, onward, youth of Zion;
Thy reward the victor&rsquo;s crown.

Hope of Israel, rise in might
With the sword of truth and right;
Sound the war-cry, &ldquo;Watch and pray!&rdquo;
Vanquish ev&rsquo;ry foe today.

We serve the living God,
And want his foes to know
That, if but few, we&rsquo;re great;
Who&rsquo;s on the Lord&rsquo;s side? Who?
We&rsquo;re going on to win;
No fear must blanch the brow.
The Lord of Hosts is ours;
Who&rsquo;s on the Lord&rsquo;s side? Who?

Go to ev&rsquo;ry tribe and nation;
Visit ev&rsquo;ry land and clime.
Sound to all the proclamation;
Tell to all the truth sublime:
That the gospel, That the gospel
Does in ancient glory shine.

Be fixed in your purpose, for Satan will try you;
The weight of your calling he perfectly knows.
Your path may be thorny, but Jesus is nigh you;
His arm is sufficient, tho demons oppose.
His arm is sufficient, tho demons oppose.

I&rsquo;ll go where you want me to go, dear Lord,
Over mountain or plain or sea;
I&rsquo;ll say what you want me to say, dear Lord;
I&rsquo;ll be what you want me to be.

