The works of God continue,
And worlds and lives abound;
Improvement and progression
Have one eternal round.
There is no end to matter;
There is no end to space;
There is no end to spirit;
There is no end to race.

There is no end to virtue;
There is no end to might;
There is no end to wisdom;
There is no end to light.
There is no end to union;
There is no end to youth;
There is no end to priesthood;
There is no end to truth.

There is no end to glory;
There is no end to love;
There is no end to being;
There is no death above.
There is no end to glory;
There is no end to love;
There is no end to being;
There is no death above.

Come, let us go up to his house;
We&rsquo;ll make our covenants and say:
&ldquo;All we are giv&rsquo;n we give to thee.
Accept our love; we will obey.
Accept our love; we will obey.&rdquo;

Turn your hearts toward your parents&mdash;
Generations gone before.
May you seek until you find them;
In the temple seal and bind them
To your hearts forevermore.

Teach me to walk in the light of his love;
Teach me to pray to my Father above;
Teach me to know of the things that are right;
Teach me, teach me to walk in the light.

In our lovely Deseret,
Where the Saints of God have met,
There&rsquo;s a multitude of children all around.
They are generous and brave;
They have precious souls to save;
They must listen and obey the gospel&rsquo;s sound.

As sisters in Zion, we&rsquo;ll all work together;
The blessings of God on our labors we&rsquo;ll seek.
We&rsquo;ll build up his kingdom with earnest endeavor;
We&rsquo;ll comfort the weary and strengthen the weak.

Ye elders of Israel, come join now with me
And seek out the righteous, where&rsquo;er they may be&mdash;
In desert, on mountain, on land, or on sea&mdash;
And bring them to Zion, the pure and the free.

It is ours, the total armor&mdash;
Priesthood held by Christ, our Lord&mdash;
If, as brethren, we are worthy
Of the Spirit&rsquo;s whispered word.

Come, come, ye Saints, no toil nor labor fear;
But with joy wend your way.
Though hard to you this journey may appear,
Grace shall be as your day.
&rsquo;Tis better far for us to strive
Our useless cares from us to drive;
Do this, and joy your hearts will swell&mdash;
All is well! All is well!

We&rsquo;ll find the place which God for us prepared,
Far away in the West,
Where none shall come to hurt or make afraid;
There the Saints will be blessed.
We&rsquo;ll make the air with music ring,
Shout praises to our God and King;
Above the rest these words we&rsquo;ll tell&mdash;
All is well! All is well!

Go to island, vale, and mountain;
There fulfill the great command;
Gather out the sons of Jacob
To possess the promised land.

I need thee, oh, I need thee;
